Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.93,0:00:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to prosper while so far apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.89,0:00:06.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As their numbers multiply,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.57,0:00:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko calls out for her special someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.81,0:00:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recognizing that single truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.39,0:00:11.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.03,0:00:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.59,0:02:34.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko's Red Handkerchief, Part Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.43,0:02:38.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.14,0:02:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? It was you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.31,0:02:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ones who found the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.44,0:02:50.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you all done something which caused\Na curse to be placed upon your souls?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.32,0:02:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course we haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.99,0:02:56.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's the kind you don't know about yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.87,0:02:58.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're not cursed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, excuse me. Did you all know that guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.91,0:03:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we just met him earlier today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.58,0:03:09.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He asked us to deliver a message to\Nthe Akagi Inn by the train station.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.13,0:03:10.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next time we saw him was here, stabbed in the chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.55,0:03:12.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of message?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.76,0:03:16.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he was the Assistant Director on a TV drama\Ncalled "The Maple Leaves of Winter," then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.93,0:03:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know "The Maple Leaves of Winter"! I know it well!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.43,0:03:27.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a romance drama that's being reaired\Non a local Gunma station now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.11,0:03:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My grandmother suggested it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.11,0:03:33.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The Maple Leaves of Winter!" "The Maple Leaves of Winter!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.82,0:03:37.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I started watching and I'm totally hooked!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.91,0:03:42.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every Saturday night from 9:00 to 10:00, I always watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.45,0:03:45.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, with today being Saturday,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.41,0:03:47.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.54,0:03:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had to bring my portable TV so I could watch some of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.42,0:03:54.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm recording it from home, too, but\NI just couldn't wait that long!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.93,0:03:58.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and his message?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.26,0:04:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah, he said there was a fan who wanted to see the\Noriginal maple tree where the red handkerchief was tied.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.48,0:04:13.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then told us to leave a message at the Akagi Inn,\Nwhere the fan was staying, saying he found the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.19,0:04:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How lazy of him, he could have done it himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.24,0:04:22.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, did you meet the fan?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.46,0:04:22.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.29,0:04:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko left a message in the guest book.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.91,0:04:33.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I found the tree you seek. Meet me\Nat the rock used for the last scene."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.84,0:04:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you signed it as "Hozumi" in katakana, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.13,0:04:40.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Why in katakana?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.97,0:04:43.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dunno, just what he said to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.02,0:04:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.90,0:04:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.27,0:04:49.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it was because he used katakana often?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.73,0:04:54.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, this is the planner we found on the way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.48,0:04:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Hozumi" is written in katakana here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.90,0:05:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found it about 100 meters away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.82,0:05:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We saw the blood on it and ran here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.88,0:05:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Blood? On it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.25,0:05:10.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when we made it, he was lying there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.29,0:05:15.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, nothing in the planner...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.38,0:05:18.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,April 1st is marked with blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.13,0:05:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,April 1st... April 1st is April Fools... April Fool...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.48,0:05:30.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.56,0:05:31.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.29,0:05:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that be a dying message?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.82,0:05:37.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there was blood on his finger, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.78,0:05:38.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yamamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.99,0:05:43.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The estimated time of death is 5:00 this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.87,0:05:48.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His wounds indicate he was stabbed\Nin the abdomen and then the chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.04,0:05:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't find any ID on him, so the culprit probably took it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.58,0:05:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.42,0:05:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All we have to do is contact the staff\Nof "The Maple Leaves of Winter"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.17,0:06:02.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and ask about the Assistant Director, Hozumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.76,0:06:06.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, one officer just reported that\Nhe found an empty tent near by.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.26,0:06:10.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An empty tent? That sounds suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.92,0:06:13.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look into that immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.10,0:06:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.48,0:06:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, did that officer mention anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.94,0:06:21.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like seeing lots of suspicious people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.11,0:06:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, all he mentioned was the tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.66,0:06:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forget about that tent, why aren't you at the Akagi Inn?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.29,0:06:31.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is where the last scene was filmed,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.75,0:06:34.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the fan he planned to meet should be suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.62,0:06:37.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is where they filmed the last scene of the drama?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.46,0:06:38.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.84,0:06:42.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the final scene, the officer was\Nleaning against that rock and she...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.26,0:06:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop stop! Stop now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.80,0:06:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm still in the middle of the drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:49.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't spoil it for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.35,0:06:57.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fifty-three people? All staying here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.44,0:06:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we're fortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.52,0:07:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, what about those who came this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.49,0:07:06.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.87,0:07:08.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember what he said?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.74,0:07:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He told us the fan sent him a message\Nthat they'd already checked in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.83,0:07:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.25,0:07:16.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, did someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.79,0:07:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.34,0:07:22.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are the three who checked in this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.09,0:07:27.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, is it possible to bring them here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.10,0:07:29.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.77,0:07:32.83,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This is an annoyance...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.84,0:07:33.46,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ohkuma Isamu (25)\NGuest
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.77,0:07:36.10,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The police here this late? Something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.79,0:07:36.42,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Watanuki Tatsuzou (63)\NGuest
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.92,0:07:39.48,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hans Burkly (41)\NGuest
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.15,0:07:38.86,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Do you all have business here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.73,0:07:46.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, I was just wondering where you\Nthree where at 5:00 this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.20,0:07:48.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was asleep in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.45,0:07:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.20,0:07:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was walking outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.58,0:07:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there anyone who can confirm those?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.16,0:07:55.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.16,0:07:57.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was using the bath in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.21,0:07:58.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't meet anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.17,0:08:01.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A young guy with a rough personality,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.50,0:08:03.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,an old man with glasses,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.42,0:08:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and a foreigner who wrote his name in katakana.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.97,0:08:10.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran, isn't that guy with the nose ring suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.68,0:08:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably can't read kanji and\Nrequested he write in katakana.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.94,0:08:19.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about that old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.19,0:08:23.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kanji may be hard on his eyes, so\Nhe could have requested katakana.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.64,0:08:24.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.24,0:08:26.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, it could be the foreigner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.86,0:08:31.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lot of foreigners likely can't read kanji, but\Nsome recognize hiragana or katakana.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.95,0:08:36.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, among you three, who has heard of a drama\Ntitled "The Maple Leaves of Winter"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.00,0:08:38.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hell's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.37,0:08:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.63,0:08:43.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't maple leaves dry up in winter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.50,0:08:47.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see! You all are just pretending!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.72,0:08:52.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, if you're a big fan, you'll\Nreact in some way to the opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.26,0:08:54.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, behold!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.02,0:08:56.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The Maple Leaves of Winter"!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.39,0:09:00.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, here we go: The European Karate Championship!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.52,0:09:05.32,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Tonight's airing of episode eight from "The\NMaple Leaves of Winter" will be postponed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.18,0:09:02.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.02,0:09:05.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A special!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.90,0:09:07.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're supposed to watch karate?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.32,0:09:12.03,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,But, naturally, the spotlight is\Non him tonight: Kyougoku Mokato.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.11,0:09:08.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.78,0:09:11.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.25,0:09:16.03,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Let's check out his intro video.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.95,0:09:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me see that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.21,0:09:20.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,At just 18 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.22,0:09:22.62,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He's from Japan, Kyougoku Mokato.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.46,0:09:24.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.09,0:09:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Sonoko, didn't Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} tell you about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.63,0:09:34.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said: "I would rather commit seppuku\Nthan lose a match in front of you."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.35,0:09:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't he so sweet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.64,0:09:38.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Seppuku?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.31,0:09:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not like he'd lose anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.19,0:09:41.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yamamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.31,0:09:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We contacted the drama's production company.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.98,0:09:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said there was no Assistant Director named Hozumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.74,0:09:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a copy of the staff list I got from a part-time employee.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.95,0:09:53.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A copy of the staff list...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.37,0:09:57.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this list right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.41,0:09:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dates are mixed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.79,0:10:01.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, here at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.25,0:10:02.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.21,0:10:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! The dates!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.04,0:10:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if we consider the part-time employee told the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.97,0:10:11.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it means the victim was lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.84,0:10:12.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.14,0:10:16.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, April Fools' is the day you can lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.97,0:10:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the culprit is lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.85,0:10:24.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, Yamamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it could mean the victim was lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.86,0:10:27.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Sonoko, would you listen to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.82,0:10:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Conanâ€”Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.36,0:10:32.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}? Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.83,0:10:38.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If my reasoning is correct...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.08,0:10:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit hasn't found it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.84,0:10:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.72,0:10:54.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ground's still soft.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.72,0:10:57.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, Hozumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was digging here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.85,0:10:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until the culprit found him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.77,0:11:04.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.35,0:11:06.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The maple leaf of winter...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.94,0:11:08.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was simply to mark this grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.74,0:11:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, where are you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.83,0:11:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.24,0:11:22.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.37,0:11:25.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was having trouble finding\Na gift for Genta and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.33,0:11:30.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm having Professor Agasa come get me, so don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.38,0:11:33.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, how can I not be worried!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.88,0:11:37.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, are those three guests who\Nchecked in this morning still there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.89,0:11:39.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they're still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.39,0:11:44.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's getting late, so Officer Yamamura said they would be
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.85,0:11:47.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,called in for questioning later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.35,0:11:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.48,0:11:50.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, could you put Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.98,0:11:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.40,0:11:55.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he wants to talk with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.16,0:11:58.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.91,0:12:01.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.83,0:12:05.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the tree we first thought\Nmy handerkerchief was caught on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.16,0:12:11.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was close to the rock used for the drama's final scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.67,0:12:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was about ten minutes away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.59,0:12:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That tree may have been used for the drama as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.93,0:12:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there's a red handkerchief tied\Nthere, and the branch looks well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.60,0:12:28.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot, that red handkerchief was tied there by a fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.52,0:12:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tree used for the drama is right next to the rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.36,0:12:35.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be too confusing with multiple trees to be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.15,0:12:39.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so? Thanks, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.45,0:12:40.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.24,0:12:43.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? It cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.37,0:12:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way, did the connection die?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.63,0:12:55.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.88,0:13:00.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right, I'm coming to pick up Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.97,0:13:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just talked to Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and decided that Sonoko\Nand I are going to ride home with you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.56,0:13:09.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way, I just called for the car to pick us up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.27,0:13:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shhhh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.44,0:13:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Professor, can you tell us where you're meeting Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.23,0:13:17.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were talking to him when his\Ncell phone battery suddenly died.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.70,0:13:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange, I thought I was just picking up Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.66,0:13:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm supposed to meet him at the entrance to the mountain\Nwhere "The Maple Leaves of Winter" was filmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.29,0:13:30.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Thank you, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.42,0:13:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.31,0:13:48.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should at least smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.14,0:13:51.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this the reunion you've longed for...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.19,0:13:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watanuki Tatsuzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.65,0:14:02.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know who it is that's buried there,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.74,0:14:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I do know you're the one who killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.33,0:14:10.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you marked the location with a red handkerchief, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.58,0:14:13.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, if something happened, you could easily move the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.79,0:14:17.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You chose the color red because it's harder to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.84,0:14:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not many people came here unless it was autumn, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.88,0:14:25.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But because of that handkerchief,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.64,0:14:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A drama was created and became very popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.72,0:14:30.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fans began coming here often,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.39,0:14:34.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And re-enacted the last scene with their own handkerchiefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.56,0:14:39.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of this, you were unable to find your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.15,0:14:42.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were afraid someone would find the body sooner or later,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.41,0:14:47.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so you later found Hozumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was a\Nmember of the drama's production staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.33,0:14:50.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You decided to pay him in order to seek out your tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.87,0:14:54.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as you asked, Hozumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} found the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.04,0:14:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, you two decided to meet at\Nthe rock used for the last scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.51,0:15:05.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You two agreed that after you paid\Nhim, he'd take you to the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.05,0:15:10.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, before he met with you, he came across the bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.93,0:15:15.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He dug at the base of the tree, just like you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.94,0:15:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after you two met, he tried to blackmail you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.11,0:15:23.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you didn't comply.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.03,0:15:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead, you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.24,0:15:32.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You forgot to ask him where the tree was...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.04,0:15:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you looked near that tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.25,0:15:40.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you figured it would be near the rock\Nused in "The Maple Leaves of Winter."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.30,0:15:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it wasn't near the last scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.34,0:15:49.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should have expected that since the tree you\Nwere searching for was over 500 meters away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.10,0:15:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, the staff would never shoot near the original\Ntree, since two red handkerchiefs may be in view.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.60,0:15:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, they had to avoid that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.82,0:16:05.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with the drama's staff being so appreciative to the\Noriginal handkerchief, they would never take it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.99,0:16:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boy, you're a little clever one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.74,0:16:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what would you have done if I hadn't showed?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.29,0:16:17.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would have just told the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.37,0:16:20.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, it's already stated clearly in Hozumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s planner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.92,0:16:26.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's foolish, it's just April 1st marked with blood in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.88,0:16:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, April 1st.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.05,0:16:33.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the old days, people used to remove\Ncotton from their kimono's on that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.22,0:16:39.72,Signs,,0,0,0,,April 1st
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.81,0:16:39.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is how the kanji for April 1 st is read as an\Nunusual surname in katakana: "Watanuki."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.72,0:16:39.72,Signs,,0,0,0,,Watanuki (kanji)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.21,0:16:39.72,Signs,,0,0,0,,Watanuki (katanaka)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.40,0:16:42.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, April 1st is "Watanuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.15,0:16:43.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.57,0:16:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was referring to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.40,0:16:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, the reason Hozumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwrote his name in katakana:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.78,0:16:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In kanji it's "August 1st," which is Hozumi in katakana.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The name comes from when farmers used to pick\Nears of rice on August 1st and offer it to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.57,0:17:04.58,Signs,,0,0,0,,August 1st
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.51,0:17:03.36,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We usually don't read the kanji for "August 1st" as Hozumi,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.08,0:17:04.58,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hozumi
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.40,0:17:05.46,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,So he was likely used ti using katakana.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.47,0:17:12.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beyond that, Hozumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s planner\Nwas found far away from the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.14,0:17:17.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought Hozumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died from his abdomen wound,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.27,0:17:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but then you saw him doing something with his planner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.98,0:17:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You stabbed him again, took the planner with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.07,0:17:26.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saw no significance in April 1st, and tossed it aside, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.44,0:17:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the- What the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.11,0:17:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Edogawa Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.07,0:17:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.12,0:17:42.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, but you little detective brat, do you\Nknow why I ran away from the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.46,0:17:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Noticing that it was beginning to get dark, you\Nfigured no one else would come by there today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.68,0:17:52.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that was the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.89,0:17:54.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was our plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.77,0:17:59.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forty, no, fifty... Who are they!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.23,0:18:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are my colleagues I called upon to find the tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.23,0:18:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I think we have more than enough to take on a little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.19,0:18:09.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.78,0:18:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.87,0:18:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.58,0:18:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, don't worry about that glasses-wearing brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.37,0:18:22.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.38,0:18:28.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's probably getting into something dangerous again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.15,0:18:30.67,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Kyougoku Makoto's match up is coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.26,0:18:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, he's so curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.26,0:18:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, he hasn't shown up yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.76,0:18:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope, it looks like he just got seeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.98,0:18:44.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.73,0:18:45.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.11,0:18:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran! Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.90,0:18:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.99,0:18:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The glasses brat?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.70,0:18:53.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.66,0:18:56.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are all of these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.24,0:18:57.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.04,0:18:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.91,0:19:02.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brat with the glasses, who are these people!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.91,0:19:04.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are they!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.58,0:19:05.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're not your friends, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.54,0:19:11.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, my, it seems we have three extra graves to dig.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.76,0:19:12.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's he?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.72,0:19:15.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's not friendly, for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.90,0:19:30.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.11,0:19:33.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are too many...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.20,0:19:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.45,0:19:40.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At this rate, we're not gonna make it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.41,0:19:41.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.58,0:19:44.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.00,0:19:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.38,0:19:50.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.30,0:19:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.51,0:19:54.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.26,0:19:57.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Kyougoku Makoto hasn't made it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.14,0:19:59.38,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He's been missing for thee days?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.44,0:20:02.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Then, where could he be?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.78,0:20:15.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.34,0:20:18.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you-?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.16,0:20:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.08,0:20:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The front, the front!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.21,0:20:27.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.21,0:20:28.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Behind you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.04,0:20:35.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it, I'll make you pay for this...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.10,0:20:49.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, by the time Officer Yamamura\Narrived ten minutes later, it was over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.31,0:20:53.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later, we found out those guys,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.78,0:20:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the older guy, who was a leader,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.36,0:20:58.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,were members of a dangerous gang.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.82,0:21:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the buried body was that of one of their former leaders.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.95,0:21:07.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, the old man and the victim couldn't decide\Nwho would become leader, so the old man killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.75,0:21:12.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, even if he manages to get out of prison,\Nhe would have to face the gang.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.34,0:21:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's if he can get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.22,0:22:45.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, you're a hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.18,0:22:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you flew here after sensing Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was in danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.30,0:22:53.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I just went to the place she mentioned in her mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.31,0:22:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you figured out that it was "The Maple Leaves of Winter"?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.02,0:23:01.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, my sister asked me to record it for her,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.86,0:23:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I ended up getting hooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.40,0:23:08.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I thought I put on the "eve of the eve"?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.53,0:23:10.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the part I couldn't get.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.04,0:23:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the day before Christmas Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.37,0:23:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was going to ask even if it were embarassing,\Nbut it would depreciate my manhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.13,0:23:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I set up a tent and waited...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.09,0:23:24.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I had to be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.30,0:23:27.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it too much?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.30,0:23:29.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.26,0:23:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a thoughtful guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.47,0:23:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's so great that you gave up your win streak for Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.64,0:23:39.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so touched!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.53,0:23:43.48,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The "Best 4" have all gathered here\Nat the Europa Karate Championship.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.03,0:23:47.36,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's unfortunate that Kyougoku Makoto isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.95,0:23:49.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, can we go to the Narita Airport?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.70,0:23:52.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you're going back!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.62,0:23:56.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I plan to fight the winner to see who's strongest.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.58,0:23:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, he still wants to fight.
